  "texts": [
    "The PDF plots are obtained from the graphical interface TMDplotter [20].",
    "This figure demonstrates that the change in the integrated PDFs upon introducing a cut of q 0 ∼ 1 GeV is significant, but similar across a wide range of scale values µ relevant to the measurements available at the LHC.",
    "This is consistent with the result of q s vs DY pair invariant mass obtained from LHC measurements over a wide range of pair invariant masses.",
    "Furthermore, it aligns with the non-perturbative Sudakov form factor, which is sensitive at small values of µ and changes slowly in the wide range of µ, from 100 to 500 GeV, where the LHC measurements have been performed.Figure 5 shows how the integrated PDF for down quark changes with the inclusion of the q 0 cut when the µ value is much smaller than those corresponding to the measurements from the LHC.",
    "The figure displays the integrated PDFs without and with the cut of q 0 = 1 GeV for two values of µ = 4 GeV and µ = 20 GeV which cover a much smaller range in µ than the values in the previous figure."
